The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The call memset(&custom_attr, 0, sizeof(custom_attr)); is redundant because pthread_attr_init(&custom_attr) immediately follows and initializes the pthread_attr_t object. Removing the memset will not change program behaviour on any POSIX-conforming implementation (pthread_attr_init sets the attribute object to its defaults), so this executed assignment is dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
